Sentencas: A La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) thin film was fabricated by the usual tape casting method using a doctor blade to reduce the operating temperature in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film

Sentencas: The resultant LSGM film was 130 3 pm in thickness and its relative density was over 99%.
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film

Sentencas: Also, the thin LSGM film showed a single phase, and its conductivity was 0.113 S/cm at 800 degreesC and 0.054 S/cm at 700 degreesC, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film

Sentencas: Therefore, it seemed that the thin LSGM film was suitable as an electrolyte for intermediate temperature operating SOFCs.
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film

Sentencas: Ni-SDC and La(Sr)CoO3 synthesized by spray pyrolysis were used as an anode and a cathode, respectively, and a single cell was fabricated with the thin LSGM film as an electrolyte.
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film

Sentencas: This single cell with the thin LSGM electrolyte exhibited excellent electrical performance, of which power density was over 0.7 W/cm(2) at 800 degreesC and 0.4 W/cm(2) at 700 degreesC. These results suggested that the LSGM-bused SOFCs with the thin LSGM film in this study would exhibit adequate performance at a temperature lower than 700 degreesC. (C) 2002 Elsevier Science B.V.
Titulo: Performance of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3 electrolyte film
